deregisterForVAT.title = Deregister for VAT
deregisterForVAT.p1 = To complete your deregistration, you need to know:
deregisterForVAT.bullet1 = your accounting method: standard accounting or cash accounting
deregisterForVAT.bullet2 = the value of any land or commercial property you own
deregisterForVAT.bullet3 = the value of any stock or assets you have or plan to keep

deregistrationReason.title = Why is the business deregistering from VAT?
deregistrationReason.reason.ceased = It has stopped trading
deregistrationReason.reason.belowThreshold = Annual turnover will be below £{0}
deregistrationReason.reason.other = Other

deregistrationDate.title = Does the business want to choose its own deregistration date?
deregistrationDate.p1 = The deregistration date can be up to a maximum of 3 months from today.
deregistrationDate.p2 = We will confirm the deregistration date when your request is accepted.
deregistrationDate.error.date.invalidDate = Enter a real deregistration date
deregistrationDate.error.date.past = The deregistration date must be in the future
deregistrationDate.error.date.future = The deregistration date must not be more than 3 months from today

deregistrationProperty.title = Does the business have any commercial property?
deregistrationProperty.p1 = This includes both land and buildings.

vatAccounts.title = How are the business’s VAT accounts prepared?
vatAccounts.method.standard = Standard accounting
vatAccounts.method.cash = Cash accounting
vatAccounts.description.standard = You record VAT whenever you send or receive an invoice
vatAccounts.description.cash = You record VAT whenever you make or receive a payment
vatAccounts.showMeAnExample.p1 = For example, you invoice someone in March but do not receive the money until June. If you record the VAT on this payment in:
vatAccounts.showMeAnExample.bullet1 = March, then you use standard accounting
vatAccounts.showMeAnExample.bullet2 = June, then you use cash accounting

ceasedTrading.title = The date your business ceased or will cease trading
ceasedTrading.hint = For example, 31 3 1980
ceasedTrading.error.date.noEntry = Enter the date your business ceased or will cease trading
ceasedTrading.error.date.invalidDate = Enter a real ceased trading date

optionTax.title = Has the business charged or claimed VAT on land or commercial property?
optionTax.text = You can choose to charge VAT on any income earned from renting or selling land or commercial property. This is known as ‘Option to Tax’.
optionTax.hint = What was the total value of the land or commercial property?

capitalAssets.title = Does the business intend to keep any capital assets?
capitalAssets.text.1 = This includes things like furniture, computers and equipment.
capitalAssets.totalSaleValue = What is the total value?

